liber.query.client
Class WysiwymCommand

java.lang.Object
  liber.query.client.WysiwymCommand
Direct Known Subclasses:
BrowseCommand, QueryCommand
public class WysiwymCommand
extends Object

Executed when a menu item from PopupMenu is selected. Various widgets can be shown to elicit values from the user, depending on the type of property selected. Information (if necessary) is send to the server and the feedback text is regenerated.

Version:
1.0 December 6, 2006, 1.1 November 5th, 2007
Author:
Feikje Hielkema

Method Detail

execute

public void execute()
Executes the menu item. Displays a pop-up whose structure depends on the type of property. Object properties are handled by ObjectPropertyCommand; datatype properties are divided in boolean, date, number, abstract, restricted value and string properties.

onClick

public void onClick(Widget sender)
Clicklistener on buttons. Moves values to the list on the right when clicked add in multiple value pane, or moves from right to left when clicked remove; updates graph when clicked ok, hides pop-up when click cancel, etc.
